Name:           swifty-notes-gtk
Version:        @VERSION@
Release:        1%{?dist}
Summary:        Native GTK markdown notes for Linux
License:        MIT
URL:            https://github.com/makoni/swifty-notes-gtk
Source0:        swifty-notes-gtk-@VERSION@-root.tar.gz
BuildArch:      x86_64

%description
Swifty Notes is a native GTK/libadwaita markdown notes application for Linux.
It keeps notes in plain files, supports a native Markdown preview, autosave,
drag-and-drop image import, and a storage-compatible CLI.

%prep
%setup -q -T -c
tar -xzf %{SOURCE0}

%build

%install
mkdir -p %{buildroot}
cp -a usr %{buildroot}/

%files
%license /usr/share/licenses/swifty-notes-gtk/LICENSE
/usr/bin/SwiftyNotes
%dir /usr/libexec/swifty-notes
/usr/libexec/swifty-notes/SwiftyNotes
%dir /usr/libexec/swifty-notes/swifty-notes-gtk_SwiftyNotes.resources
/usr/libexec/swifty-notes/swifty-notes-gtk_SwiftyNotes.resources/*
/usr/share/applications/me.spaceinbox.SwiftyNotes.desktop
/usr/share/icons/hicolor/scalable/apps/me.spaceinbox.SwiftyNotes.svg
/usr/share/metainfo/me.spaceinbox.SwiftyNotes.metainfo.xml

%changelog
* Tue Apr 08 2026 Sergey Armodin <makoni@users.noreply.github.com> - @VERSION@-1
- Automated release build.
